      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): retry once on token-invalid errors 99991663/99991664 with cache invalidation (fixes #97287)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #97287.\n\nWhen the cached `tenant_access_token` becomes invalid (clock drift, server-side revocation, etc.), the Feishu plugin could not send messages. Error code 99991663 (`Invalid access token`) was thrown immediately with no automatic retry, requiring manual gateway restart.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`requestFeishuApi` only retried on rate-limit errors (429, 11232, 230020). Token-invalid errors (99991663, 99991664) were not handled.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/comment-shared.ts`: Added `FEISHU_TOKEN_INVALID_CODES` (99991663, 99991664), `getFeishuTokenInvalidCode()` exporter, and `setClearAllFeishuTokenCaches()` setter (avoids circular dependency with streaming-card.ts). Modified `requestFeishuApi` to clear the token cache and retry once on first-attempt token-invalid errors.\n- `extensions/feishu/src/streaming-card.ts`: Registered `clearFeishuTokenCache()` via the setter so the module-level `tokenCache` Map is cleared on token-invalid errors.\n- `extensions/feishu/src/send.retry.test.ts`: Added 8 tests covering token-invalid detection, single retry with cache clearing, persistent failure exhaustion, and non-token non-rate-limit error preservation.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **Unit tests:** `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/feishu/src/send.retry.test.ts` — 40/40 passed\n- **Lint:** clean\n- **Lockfile:** unchanged\n\n## AI Assistance 🤖\n\n- **AI-assisted**: Yes\n- **Co-Authored-By**: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>\n- **Human confirmed understanding**: Yes\n\n## Update 2026-07-01\n\n### Code fixes\n- **Cache clearing registered at client module**: Moved `setClearAllFeishuTokenCaches` registration from `streaming-card.ts` (only loaded for streaming card path) to `client.ts` (always loaded), so normal send paths also benefit from token-invalid recovery\n- **Preserve retry error details**: Replaced generic 'unreachable' exhausted-retries error with a descriptive message\n\n### Real behavior proof\n\n**Feishu API connectivity (verified with real credentials):**\n```\n$ curl -s -X POST \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal\" ...\n{\"code\":0,\"expire\":7064,\"msg\":\"ok\",\"tenant_access_token\":\"t-g1...\"}\n```\n\n**Token-invalid error detection (via production code):**\n```\n✅ 99991663 (token invalid): 99991663 (expected 99991663)\n✅ 99991664 (token expired): 99991664 (expected 99991664)\n✅ non-token error (230001): undefined (expected undefined)\n✅ no error object: undefined (expected undefined)\n```\n\n**Unit tests (78/78 passed):**\n```\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  78 passed (78)\n```\n\n## Review\n- Manually reviewed and verified\n- AI-assisted: Yes",
        "branch": "fix/issue-97287-feishu-token-invalid-retry",
